powerfully important negative emotion is, right?

01:10:58.680 --> 01:11:02.920
That how a sense of guilt and shame and vulnerability

01:11:02.920 --> 01:11:07.840
can just pervade our entire life perspective.

01:11:07.840 --> 01:11:10.760
So all of a sudden we're swimming in a very different soup,

01:11:10.760 --> 01:11:14.160
and it's a frightening soup, and it's a toxic soup,

01:11:14.160 --> 01:11:17.120
and I'm most struck by that.

01:11:17.120 --> 01:11:20.320
And that goes along with the idea that we're not taught

01:11:20.320 --> 01:11:23.400
that emotion always beats logic.

01:11:23.400 --> 01:11:25.320
You know, like, I think the idea of Descartes,

01:11:25.320 --> 01:11:27.520
Daniel, the idea that we're rational creatures,

01:11:27.520 --> 01:11:28.960
you know, that kind of comes down to us

01:11:28.960 --> 01:11:32.480
through Western thought is like completely not true.

01:11:32.480 --> 01:11:34.720
Like we're rational creatures,

01:11:34.720 --> 01:11:38.560
only if there is an emotion grabbing for our attention,

01:11:38.560 --> 01:11:39.400
right?

01:11:39.400 --> 01:11:40.440
Like, you know, we're attending to one another,

01:11:40.440 --> 01:11:41.640
we're being very logical, right?

01:11:41.640 --> 01:11:44.880
What we're doing now, if we heard a frightening noise

01:11:44.880 --> 01:11:47.400
right outside the door, like we'd be entirely different,

01:11:47.400 --> 01:11:48.240
right?

01:11:48.240 --> 01:11:49.080
The emotion would trump everything,

01:11:49.080 --> 01:11:50.720
is they stop paying attention to this, right?

01:11:50.720 --> 01:11:53.080
Now safety is at stake, and we think differently,

01:11:53.080 --> 01:11:55.240
feel differently, behave differently, right?

01:11:55.240 --> 01:11:58.920
And this is what happens to us, not just in situations

01:11:58.920 --> 01:12:01.200
where something drags us from,

01:12:01.200 --> 01:12:03.360
yanks us from one emotional state to another,

01:12:03.360 --> 01:12:05.160
but it can be very, very pervasive.

01:12:05.160 --> 01:12:09.160
So my sense of anger, frustration, inadequacy,

01:12:09.160 --> 01:12:10.800
and then soothing in unhealthy ways,

01:12:10.800 --> 01:12:13.120
you know, soothing by drinking too much,

01:12:13.120 --> 01:12:15.160
and then kind of hating myself in the first place,

01:12:15.160 --> 01:12:16.840
and then hating the world around me,

01:12:16.840 --> 01:12:18.200
and then, you know, starting to think,

01:12:18.200 --> 01:12:19.920
well, who cares, you know, what happens?

01:12:19.920 --> 01:12:22.640
Like, you know, there's some very dark thoughts

01:12:22.640 --> 01:12:27.440
and choices that came from a changed perspective

01:12:27.440 --> 01:12:29.400
of self in the world.

01:12:29.400 --> 01:12:33.280
So what do you do in that, because of trauma,

01:12:33.280 --> 01:12:35.840
again, small or large,

01:12:35.840 --> 01:12:40.160
you find yourself swimming or drowning

01:12:40.160 --> 01:12:43.240
in a soup of negative emotion.

01:12:43.240 --> 01:12:44.080
What do you do?

01:12:45.480 --> 01:12:46.760
What do you do with that emotion?

01:12:46.760 --> 01:12:49.040
I mean, we don't have to even talk about trauma,

01:12:49.480 --> 01:12:54.160
I think the interesting thing is, you know,

01:12:55.160 --> 01:12:58.880
any one of us throughout the day can find ourselves

01:12:58.880 --> 01:13:02.520
taking a bit of a dip in the pool of negative emotion.

01:13:02.520 --> 01:13:03.960
What do we do with that?

01:13:03.960 --> 01:13:07.000
The first thing is to separate how we feel

01:13:07.000 --> 01:13:08.920
from what's true.

01:13:08.920 --> 01:13:11.280
Because we don't do a good job of that as humans.

01:13:11.280 --> 01:13:15.400
If I feel bad about myself, it's very easy to,

01:13:15.400 --> 01:13:17.920
then I conclude like, I'm bad, right?

01:13:17.920 --> 01:13:19.120
If I feel ashamed of myself,

01:13:19.120 --> 01:13:22.360
I conclude I'm a terrible person who's shameful, right?

01:13:22.360 --> 01:13:25.480
This is that, you know, there's an old psychodynamic concept

01:13:25.480 --> 01:13:27.640
of what they used to call it, an observing ego.

01:13:27.640 --> 01:13:28.800
It still gets called that.

01:13:28.800 --> 01:13:31.200
It's not ego in the sense of arrogance, right?

01:13:31.200 --> 01:13:34.880
It's the ability to step outside and to see ourselves, right?

01:13:34.880 --> 01:13:37.080
So that's what lets us keep the difference

01:13:37.080 --> 01:13:39.480
between our feelings, right?

01:13:39.480 --> 01:13:40.600
And what we know to be true.

01:13:40.600 --> 01:13:41.960
Like we could be very angry at someone.

01:13:41.960 --> 01:13:43.240
And so I think that person's terrible.

01:13:43.240 --> 01:13:44.640
I think the person's stupid.

01:13:44.640 --> 01:13:45.560
I think that right now,

01:13:45.560 --> 01:13:47.960
because like something negative just passed between us,

01:13:47.960 --> 01:13:50.320
this inside of me, it's just because of how I feel.

01:13:50.320 --> 01:13:51.760
Like when I can separate that,

01:13:51.760 --> 01:13:54.160
how do I actually think about that person, right?

01:13:54.160 --> 01:13:59.320
And, you know, we get driven so, so frequently

01:13:59.320 --> 01:14:02.640
by how we feel, because how we think,

01:14:02.640 --> 01:14:04.800
therefore what we believe, right?

01:14:04.800 --> 01:14:06.320
Just kind of comes on its heels

01:14:06.320 --> 01:14:08.760
as if the feeling is dragging it along.

01:14:08.760 --> 01:14:10.440
And I've been struck by that.

01:14:10.440 --> 01:14:14.320
It's one of the things that has struck me so the most, right?

01:14:14.440 --> 01:14:18.080
Among the very most in 20 years of working as a psychiatrist

01:14:18.080 --> 01:14:22.320
is how we are led by our feelings, our emotions,

01:14:22.320 --> 01:14:23.600
as if they are truth.

01:14:23.600 --> 01:14:25.400
And then they create truth

01:14:25.400 --> 01:14:28.960
because we embrace what they're telling us as true.

01:14:30.040 --> 01:14:32.080
And that is, I think, incredibly,

01:14:32.080 --> 01:14:33.720
I think it's how people learn prejudice.

01:14:33.720 --> 01:14:36.200
I think it's how people learn self-hatred.

01:14:36.200 --> 01:14:39.200
I think it's how we learn so many destructive behaviors.

01:14:39.200 --> 01:14:42.680
And then the blinders on us come in more and more

01:14:42.680 --> 01:14:44.120
and more and more.

01:14:44.120 --> 01:14:46.400
So separate, you know, we're driven by what we feel

01:14:46.400 --> 01:14:48.960
unless we understand that what we feel

01:14:48.960 --> 01:14:51.320
is different from what we know to be true

01:14:51.320 --> 01:14:53.480
or what we can decide on one way or another.

01:14:53.480 --> 01:14:56.840
And that requires realizing and catching

01:14:56.840 --> 01:14:59.840
the emotions themselves, realizing that it's an emotion.

01:14:59.840 --> 01:15:01.840
A feeling comes into your mind, overtakes you,

01:15:01.840 --> 01:15:06.560
a feeling of anger, dislike, hatred, all of that.

01:15:06.560 --> 01:15:08.000
It just comes in.

01:15:08.000 --> 01:15:11.080
It's like, why did that person just cut me off

01:15:11.080 --> 01:15:13.560
in traffic or something like that, that feeling?

01:15:13.560 --> 01:15:16.120
So wait, you just kind of take it as a feeling

01:15:16.120 --> 01:15:19.120
and realize it's a feeling that doesn't represent

01:15:19.120 --> 01:15:21.480
some deep reality about the world that's fundamental.

01:15:21.480 --> 01:15:26.480
Or you, they just kind of watch it and let it pass,

01:15:27.600 --> 01:15:29.800
which is the natural way of things.

01:15:29.800 --> 01:15:32.440
Yeah, we'll decide if it means anything, you know?

01:15:32.440 --> 01:15:34.280
If I'm mad, right, someone cut me off

01:15:34.280 --> 01:15:37.240
and I feel hatred and I want to destroy them, right?

01:15:37.240 --> 01:15:39.480
Just stop and think, look, I've got that in me.

01:15:39.480 --> 01:15:42.240
I can, you know, are the stressors running too high

01:15:42.280 --> 01:15:43.720
in my life, like is it really good?

01:15:43.720 --> 01:15:47.760
Should I be on this road, 10 minutes behind schedule?

01:15:47.760 --> 01:15:49.120
Like is it, what am I really doing?

01:15:49.120 --> 01:15:52.920
So we can learn, but yes, it's an observation skill, right?

01:15:52.920 --> 01:15:56.200
And it's an observation skill that we can develop, you know?

01:15:56.200 --> 01:15:58.480
I often think about, you know, there was something called

01:15:58.480 --> 01:16:01.840
the tapestry theory, which I think initially was a theodicy

01:16:01.840 --> 01:16:04.280
of explaining, I believe this is true.

01:16:04.280 --> 01:16:06.520
I'm not sure of this, that the idea was that,

01:16:06.520 --> 01:16:11.160
oh, we don't see God's plan because we're up too close

01:16:11.160 --> 01:16:12.000
to it, right?

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:14.200
Like as if there was a beautiful tapestry on the wall

01:16:14.200 --> 01:16:15.480
and we're standing right up it,

01:16:15.480 --> 01:16:17.640
we're only gonna see one part of it,

01:16:17.640 --> 01:16:19.040
we need to stand back from it.

01:16:19.040 --> 01:16:21.760
And, you know, I remember learning that religion studies

01:16:21.760 --> 01:16:24.680
class made me really fascinated with that at the time.

01:16:24.680 --> 01:16:28.440
And I think that there are a lot of things we do that about,

01:16:28.440 --> 01:16:29.280
right?

01:16:29.280 --> 01:16:32.280
And in training ourselves to have an observing ego,

01:16:32.280 --> 01:16:36.200
what we're saying is, hey, like just the busyness of life

01:16:36.200 --> 01:16:39.360
or my own impulses or the pool of emotions are trying

01:16:39.400 --> 01:16:41.640
to pull me up right close to whatever tapestry

01:16:41.640 --> 01:16:42.480
there is there.

01:16:42.480 --> 01:16:43.320
And I want to sort of resist that.

01:16:43.320 --> 01:16:47.600
I mean, I'm better off if I really stay further behind it.

01:16:47.600 --> 01:16:50.400
And then I make a choice if I want to come close to it.

01:16:50.400 --> 01:16:52.200
If there's some really positive emotion,

01:16:52.200 --> 01:16:54.600
it's friendship, it's love, it's nurturing,

01:16:54.600 --> 01:16:57.160
you know what, let me come right up to this, right?

01:16:57.160 --> 01:16:59.600
But I want to choose when I'm doing that.

01:16:59.600 --> 01:17:01.920
I don't want some drive.

01:17:01.920 --> 01:17:04.320
I didn't decide to like take me by the back of the head

01:17:04.320 --> 01:17:07.320
and put me up against that tapestry.

01:17:07.360 --> 01:17:11.360
So the interesting exercise for me,

01:17:11.360 --> 01:17:13.640
and I think for a lot of people in modern civilization

01:17:13.640 --> 01:17:16.280
is the internet with social media,

01:17:16.280 --> 01:17:20.040
that it's almost like going to the gym or something like that.

01:17:20.040 --> 01:17:21.640
At least that's the way I see it.

01:17:21.640 --> 01:17:26.040
Because there's a bunch of forces on social media

01:17:26.040 --> 01:17:28.920
that are trying to make you feel things.

01:17:28.920 --> 01:17:33.560
Most of it is kind of in the negative space of feelings.

01:17:33.560 --> 01:17:36.920
Because there is actually a strong gravity pull

01:17:36.920 --> 01:17:39.080
to negative feelings for some reason.

01:17:39.080 --> 01:17:42.640
And so the, and the brain notices them more.

01:17:42.640 --> 01:17:45.080
I don't know what that pull is, but it's there.

01:17:45.080 --> 01:17:46.720
And you get to observe it on social media.

01:17:46.720 --> 01:17:49.520
Like if you actually just scroll through social media,

01:17:50.760 --> 01:17:54.680
you feel the gravitational pull of negative emotions.

01:17:54.680 --> 01:17:58.480
And I just see it as a kind of exercise of like,

01:17:58.480 --> 01:18:00.400
you feel the pull just like when you go to the gym,

01:18:00.400 --> 01:18:01.640
there's a resistance.

01:18:01.640 --> 01:18:05.160
And I practice like a stepping way to look at the tapestry,

01:18:06.040 --> 01:18:07.280
and there's different mechanisms

01:18:07.280 --> 01:18:09.120
I think all of us have to learn.

01:18:09.120 --> 01:18:11.480
For me, there's a kind of,

01:18:11.480 --> 01:18:14.720
you mentioned gratitude and humility.

01:18:15.760 --> 01:18:20.040
So like if somebody, if it's me personally,

01:18:20.040 --> 01:18:23.160
I've recently gotten attacked, if you place it here and there.

01:18:24.920 --> 01:18:27.320
If they're saying that they're much smarter than me,

01:18:27.320 --> 01:18:30.040
I practice kind of humility, like you mentioned.

01:18:30.040 --> 01:18:33.040
And I kind of imagine that they are smarter than me.

01:18:33.040 --> 01:18:34.880
Those things like helped me to kind of like,

01:18:34.880 --> 01:18:38.200
pull away and then maybe they have a lesson to teach me.

01:18:38.200 --> 01:18:42.280
Like I don't take their sort of negative comments to heart,

01:18:42.280 --> 01:18:43.600
but I imagine the human being

01:18:43.600 --> 01:18:46.360
and like that they might have a lesson to teach me.

01:18:46.360 --> 01:18:48.480
And in general, when it's more amorphous,

01:18:48.480 --> 01:18:49.680
kind of negative feeling,

01:18:49.680 --> 01:18:52.160
I'll think the other thing is that gratitude.

01:18:52.160 --> 01:18:54.760
Just like different versions,

01:18:54.760 --> 01:18:57.560
almost memifiable versions of like,

01:18:57.560 --> 01:18:59.000
oh, this is pretty cool.

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:00.560
Like we got a thing going here.

01:19:00.560 --> 01:19:01.800
There's like human civilization,

01:19:02.640 --> 01:19:06.920
bickering and having a little fun like lunch, food fight.

01:19:06.920 --> 01:19:08.080
And it's kind of cool.

01:19:08.080 --> 01:19:09.920
Like we get to interact in this way

01:19:09.920 --> 01:19:12.680
and there's a bit of humor.

01:19:12.680 --> 01:19:13.920
There's like Thanksgiving dinner.

01:19:13.920 --> 01:19:16.160
Like if you, like Thanksgiving dinner,

01:19:16.160 --> 01:19:17.600
if you're arguing about politics,

01:19:17.600 --> 01:19:19.000
you can feel like really intense.

01:19:19.000 --> 01:19:20.280
Like I can't believe you said this,

01:19:20.280 --> 01:19:22.640
but if you zoom out, it's like family.

01:19:22.640 --> 01:19:24.520
This is like, this is amazing.

01:19:24.520 --> 01:19:27.440
So that kind of feeling really helps.

01:19:27.440 --> 01:19:29.880
But it's like, it really is like going to the gym.

01:19:29.880 --> 01:19:32.000
It's like building up a muscle

01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:36.120
to be able to pull away from those emotions.

01:19:36.120 --> 01:19:38.720
I don't think I get to practice

01:19:38.720 --> 01:19:41.080
that kind of emotion in regular day-to-day life.

01:19:41.080 --> 01:19:43.520
Cause like, it's hard to get those reps.

01:19:43.520 --> 01:19:45.560
On social media, you can really get the reps in.

01:19:45.560 --> 01:19:46.400
It's kind of cool.

01:19:46.400 --> 01:19:48.600
Like that's the way I see social media

01:19:48.600 --> 01:19:51.680
is a chance to sort of practice that stoicism

01:19:51.680 --> 01:19:54.240
of like, of gratitude, of humility,

01:19:54.240 --> 01:19:56.160
of loving other people in the face

01:19:56.160 --> 01:19:58.160
of this negative emotion, all that.

01:19:58.160 --> 01:20:01.920
Yes, and, you know, there's a certain kind of psychotherapy

01:20:01.920 --> 01:20:04.200
that talks a lot about this idea that like,

01:20:04.200 --> 01:20:06.200
oh, everything is as it should be, right?

01:20:06.200 --> 01:20:09.600
Which doesn't mean from some moral or justice point.

01:20:09.600 --> 01:20:12.160
It's just that often if you look at things,

01:20:13.240 --> 01:20:16.040
one thing leads to another to another to another

01:20:16.040 --> 01:20:19.040
in a way that's actually very, very predictable,

01:20:19.040 --> 01:20:21.600
even though we might be surprised about it, right?

01:20:21.600 --> 01:20:26.600
And so an example, so I would say that gratitude often does

01:20:27.440 --> 01:20:30.200
come along with a healthy pride, right?

01:20:30.200 --> 01:20:33.400
So you could say in the example you gave,

01:20:33.400 --> 01:20:36.360
I'm being assailed on social media, okay?

01:20:36.360 --> 01:20:39.200
So you could say, well, you know, there was a time I sat at,

01:20:39.200 --> 01:20:42.560
I set forth to impact people, right?

01:20:42.560 --> 01:20:46.200
To be able to reach people and to impact them, right?

01:20:46.200 --> 01:20:49.400
And look, I feel a sense of both gratitude and pride

01:20:49.400 --> 01:20:50.640
that I've done that, right?

01:20:50.640 --> 01:20:53.680
Because look, you did it because of your effort, right?

01:20:53.680 --> 01:20:55.400
Your work, your intelligence, your thoughts,

01:20:55.400 --> 01:20:57.480
like you're responsible for it, right?

01:20:57.480 --> 01:21:01.400
But also you feel gratitude because any one of us

01:21:01.400 --> 01:21:03.040
who's here and has any opportunity

01:21:03.040 --> 01:21:05.240
has reason to feel immense gratitude, right?

01:21:05.240 --> 01:21:08.080
So then you can say, okay, what's actually gone on here

01:21:08.080 --> 01:21:09.600
is something successful.

01:21:09.600 --> 01:21:13.600
I set out to do something and I'm doing it, right?

01:21:14.640 --> 01:21:19.200
And what it brings with it absolutely includes being assailed.

01:21:19.200 --> 01:21:20.600
There's no surprise there, right?

01:21:20.600 --> 01:21:25.000
That because of, you know, people who have anything good

01:21:25.000 --> 01:21:27.160
to serve as lightning rods for envy.

01:21:27.160 --> 01:21:30.880
So then, yes, there will be people who want to make up lies

01:21:30.880 --> 01:21:32.040
or whatever they want to do

01:21:32.040 --> 01:21:34.520
because you become a lightning rod for envy

01:21:34.520 --> 01:21:37.520
by having succeeded at the thing you set out to do

01:21:37.520 --> 01:21:40.880
about which you can feel a healthy pride and gratitude, right?

01:21:40.880 --> 01:21:43.560
And then I think that kind of puts it in its place.

01:21:43.560 --> 01:21:45.280
I mean, you're still gonna make decisions about it,

01:21:45.280 --> 01:21:47.120
but it makes sense then,

01:21:47.120 --> 01:21:49.920
like you have a mechanism of understanding it

01:21:49.920 --> 01:21:52.360
that not only makes sense to you,

01:21:52.360 --> 01:21:56.480
but reflects the truth of what you actually have done

01:21:56.480 --> 01:21:58.920
and achieved and what's going on in the world around you.

01:21:58.920 --> 01:22:01.840
Well, I wonder if we're all kind of a little bit unique

01:22:01.840 --> 01:22:03.120
in this because for me,

01:22:04.520 --> 01:22:06.400
I mean, maybe it's useful to kind of talk

01:22:06.400 --> 01:22:10.800
through my own experience of it is for me,

01:22:10.800 --> 01:22:13.160
I try to avoid, especially in those situations,

01:22:13.160 --> 01:22:18.160
to feel pride because I'm just looking empirically.

01:22:19.160 --> 01:22:23.120
I feel way happier if I focus on humility.

01:22:23.120 --> 01:22:25.920
If I ever think of like,

01:22:25.920 --> 01:22:28.280
oh yeah, when you do something meaningful

01:22:28.280 --> 01:22:29.920
or you become more popular,

01:22:29.920 --> 01:22:31.520
you're going to experience these kinds of,

01:22:31.520 --> 01:22:33.320
I feel the attacks more

01:22:33.320 --> 01:22:36.080
and it's like me versus the world.

01:22:36.080 --> 01:22:37.720
That's the feeling that you start getting

01:22:37.720 --> 01:22:40.000
and that does not create a pleasant feeling.

01:22:40.000 --> 01:22:43.880
So to me, the pleasant feeling is like stepping away,

01:22:43.880 --> 01:22:47.120
like kind of laughing at it at all with a smile

01:22:47.160 --> 01:22:49.200
and not like in a negative, like laughing at people

01:22:49.200 --> 01:22:52.080
but just like laughing at the theater of it,

01:22:52.080 --> 01:22:52.920
the circus of it,

01:22:52.920 --> 01:22:55.320
like this whole absurd existence we've got going on

01:22:55.320 --> 01:22:57.720
and then just having a humility in like,

01:22:57.720 --> 01:22:59.200
everybody has a lesson to teach me.

01:22:59.200 --> 01:23:00.520
It just makes me feel good.

01:23:00.520 --> 01:23:03.760
The pride thing I do like feeling

01:23:05.800 --> 01:23:07.800
in a positive pool of emotion.

01:23:07.800 --> 01:23:11.200
So if I'm building a trinket and I finish it,

01:23:11.200 --> 01:23:12.640
I'm like really happy with myself.

01:23:12.640 --> 01:23:13.760
Like I finished this thing

01:23:13.760 --> 01:23:16.880
and I usually actually like to do that alone.

01:23:16.880 --> 01:23:18.600
Like I don't need an audience for pride.

