01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:51.840
You could.

01:25:51.840 --> 01:25:54.360
It may not be easy, but there's a lot of plasticity

01:25:54.360 --> 01:25:56.360
and a lot of pliability there.

01:25:56.360 --> 01:25:57.880
Across all ages.

01:25:58.960 --> 01:26:01.320
People are different and there may be idiosyncrasies

01:26:01.320 --> 01:26:03.160
of why one person is in a different place.

01:26:03.160 --> 01:26:05.960
But as a general rule, I think the answer is absolutely yes.

01:26:05.960 --> 01:26:08.600
I mean, people have evolved and I've worked with people

01:26:08.600 --> 01:26:10.600
who've really changed themselves

01:26:10.600 --> 01:26:12.520
and brought in their conception and understanding,

01:26:12.520 --> 01:26:14.600
you know, they're in their 80s or, you know,

01:26:14.600 --> 01:26:16.520
I think we can do it at any stage of life.

01:26:16.520 --> 01:26:21.360
And I would make a case for, for intracyclic.

01:26:21.360 --> 01:26:23.960
So not between people necessarily, right?

01:26:23.960 --> 01:26:26.480
But inside of oneself or the feeling of pride.

01:26:26.480 --> 01:26:28.200
And maybe if we call it self-esteem, right?

01:26:28.200 --> 01:26:30.320
Like let's say we call it self-esteem, right?

01:26:30.320 --> 01:26:31.840
Or we could call it healthy pride.

01:26:31.840 --> 01:26:33.320
We could put either word to it.

01:26:33.320 --> 01:26:36.160
But if you think about what we're trying to avoid

01:26:36.160 --> 01:26:38.720
is say a sense of inadequacy,

01:26:38.720 --> 01:26:42.040
then it is good to sort of own what's ours.

01:26:42.040 --> 01:26:44.720
We can put ourselves a little bit out of balance

01:26:45.800 --> 01:26:47.680
either in terms of building up resentments

01:26:47.680 --> 01:26:50.640
or in terms of decreasing self-confidence, right?

01:26:50.640 --> 01:26:54.120
If we're not owning everything, that's ours, right?

01:26:54.120 --> 01:26:56.880
So a thought, thought I would have about,

01:26:57.880 --> 01:27:00.720
let's say about some pride or some self-esteem, right?

01:27:00.720 --> 01:27:03.800
Is it can work against vulnerability, right?

01:27:03.800 --> 01:27:06.160
Which we know can also in some situations

01:27:06.160 --> 01:27:09.280
push us towards jumping the boundary into envy

01:27:09.280 --> 01:27:10.120
and all of that.

01:27:10.120 --> 01:27:12.280
So think about vulnerability.

01:27:12.280 --> 01:27:16.720
If you conceive, okay, people are assailing me

01:27:16.720 --> 01:27:20.160
and you just go to a place of gratitude,

01:27:20.160 --> 01:27:24.120
you know, it can send a message that,

01:27:24.120 --> 01:27:26.800
okay, I'm just lucky and I hope I continue to get lucky

01:27:26.800 --> 01:27:29.000
as opposed to like, that's not true, right?

01:27:29.000 --> 01:27:31.640
Like there's ability inside of me

01:27:31.640 --> 01:27:34.080
and discernment inside of me that tells me

01:27:34.080 --> 01:27:36.240
I can have a greater sense of confidence

01:27:36.240 --> 01:27:38.880
that I'll navigate what comes my way, right?

01:27:38.880 --> 01:27:42.100
So because the pride or the self-esteem part

01:27:42.100 --> 01:27:44.040
is owning what we've contributed

01:27:44.040 --> 01:27:46.200
to the goodness we've created, right?

01:27:46.200 --> 01:27:49.760
Which does in a sense helps us feel better about ourselves.

01:27:49.760 --> 01:27:52.600
And it also helps us feel armed against say

01:27:52.600 --> 01:27:54.800
the slings and arrows of, you know,

01:27:54.800 --> 01:27:57.040
whatever outrageous fortune may come next.

01:27:57.040 --> 01:27:58.880
I don't know, I don't know, I don't know.

