I'll give you an example of a person

02:22:56.040 --> 02:22:58.600
who would not let me help him.

02:22:58.600 --> 02:22:59.680
It was a young man.

02:22:59.680 --> 02:23:02.360
So when I was in training, who was very, very sick

02:23:02.360 --> 02:23:05.760
and needed to change certain choices and habits

02:23:05.760 --> 02:23:07.560
or he was not gonna survive.

02:23:07.560 --> 02:23:11.640
And I had no ability to help him whatsoever.

02:23:11.640 --> 02:23:13.320
And I went and I saw a supervisor

02:23:13.320 --> 02:23:14.800
who was existentially trained.

02:23:14.800 --> 02:23:16.880
We're here, it's different from existentialism

02:23:16.880 --> 02:23:17.920
in the classic sense,

02:23:17.920 --> 02:23:20.440
but it's about really human connection, right?

02:23:20.440 --> 02:23:23.560
And the guy was always wanting to teach me something, right?

02:23:23.560 --> 02:23:25.160
Cause I can get by in Spanish,

02:23:25.160 --> 02:23:26.400
but he was fluent in Spanish.

02:23:26.400 --> 02:23:28.880
And he wanted to, he'd, oh, you traveled here

02:23:28.880 --> 02:23:31.560
and he'd say, you know, a word to see if I knew.

02:23:31.560 --> 02:23:34.080
And I was always directing back to what I was supposed to do,

02:23:34.080 --> 02:23:34.920
right?

02:23:34.920 --> 02:23:35.760
And the supervisor, I'll never forget,

02:23:35.760 --> 02:23:37.880
he said, let him teach you Spanish.

02:23:37.880 --> 02:23:39.320
Like, okay, come on.

02:23:39.320 --> 02:23:41.200
So we had a couple of sessions where if you looked

02:23:41.200 --> 02:23:43.040
from the outside, he said, what is going on there?

02:23:43.040 --> 02:23:45.840
Like, right, like this, it was their Spanish lessons

02:23:45.840 --> 02:23:46.920
to me, right?

02:23:46.920 --> 02:23:49.400
And then at some point he had, he brought in his mother

02:23:49.400 --> 02:23:51.440
and it was, he hadn't brought her in yet.

02:23:51.440 --> 02:23:54.920
And he was in part showing off that he taught me something,

02:23:54.920 --> 02:23:55.760
right?

02:23:55.760 --> 02:23:58.160
And I said a couple of things and he felt more powerful.

02:23:58.160 --> 02:24:00.120
Like he was younger than me and he felt sick

02:24:00.120 --> 02:24:02.760
and disempowered, but he didn't feel that way

02:24:02.760 --> 02:24:03.960
once he taught me something

02:24:03.960 --> 02:24:06.200
and we showed it off to his mother, right?

02:24:06.200 --> 02:24:07.880
And his behavior started to change.

02:24:07.880 --> 02:24:10.000
He started taking better care of himself.

02:24:10.000 --> 02:24:11.960
He could see a little more what I was saying.

02:24:12.000 --> 02:24:13.360
He was like, you're a wonderful person.

02:24:13.360 --> 02:24:15.880
Look, you love your mother and your aunt and they love you.

02:24:15.880 --> 02:24:18.400
And like, look, he could start seeing that about himself.

02:24:18.400 --> 02:24:20.160
But that came from humanness.

02:24:20.160 --> 02:24:23.760
And I think that's the way we help people.

02:24:23.760 --> 02:24:25.800
I don't understand why we don't do everything that way.

